ens","Donbass Battalion","Donetsk Oblast","Eastern Ukraine","irregular volunteer battalions","Kiev","Kryvbas","Lededyns’ke","MON 90","pro-Russian separatist","propaganda","Russian Federation","Sakhanka","Satana","Shyrokyne","TM-62","Ukrainian Insurgent Army","Ukrainian Marines","Ukrainian National Guard","Urzuf","UXO","Vodyane","Volunteer fighters"],"articleSection":["War Stories"],"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"CommentAction","name":"Comment","target":["https://sofrep.com/news/going-gonzo-in-ukraine-part-1/#respond"]}]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://sofrep.com/#/schema/person/b8c43daeeb4fc019edea0aac94405884","name":"Buck Clay","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https://sofrep.com/#/schema/person/image/","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/22b1a5d3f8d68838a4c23d8f233e94c8?s=96&d=mm&r=r","contentUrl":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/22b1a5d3f8d68838a4c23d8f233e94c8?s=96&d=mm&r=r","caption":"Buck Clay"},"description":"is an American. He served eleven years for God and Country with the illustrious Airborne Combat Engineers and dedicated four of those years traveling to wonderful faraway lands where he dug around in the dirt looking for bombs. After much soul searching, he decided to return to academia. There he obtained two additional university degrees, and he is now pursuing a fourth - because university is fun. Currently, he travels around quite a bit, and finds comfort on sunny desert mountaintops and seaside resorts where people try to kill him.","sameAs":["https://www.linkedin.com/pub/robert-buck-clay/49/324/a32","https://twitter.com/buck_clay"],"url":"https://sofrep.com/author/buck-clay/"}]}</script>

